I received my Zeagoo Men's Faux Leather Trousers in the mail, earlier yesterday, and I'm very pleased with the way these pants fit. I have a rather difficult time finding pants that are of smaller fitting size in  the American retail spectrum, so I was quite happy to find that these size 28 faux leather trousers fit nicely around my legs and decently enough in the waist area (I actually have some breathing room, believe it or not.) This is truly an excellent bargain to come by. Most of the 28" x 32" pants that I've purchased here in the states (skinny jeans or otherwise,) are constantly sliding off of me, but these trousers remedy these issues effortlessly!

If you have a naturally small (Western) frame, and you are stumped for finding clothing pieces that will justify your wardrobe, stateside, look to Asia for a new edge in your personal style. Paying attention to the Asian fitting chart will benefit you greatly, if you decide to order this product.

Yes, it's true, these pants do give off a mild odor, but I'm sure it will subside--the materials used to make this clothing, are after all, factory made.

Either way, this will make a convincing costume piece for my eighties post apocalyptic warrior outfit this upcoming Halloween, and as clothing article to wear out to the city.
summary: Great For A Mad Max-type costume or as a rock 'n roll accessory

Only taking off one star because it lacks the release mechanism when the spring is taut.  Just don't go nuts winding it when you first get it, 20-30 winds seem fair.  As long as you don't damage a gear over winding it, this seems a perfect watch for its price, style, and mechanism.  The auto-mechanism seems to be working well keeping it wound, the cost is just right, and I would recommend this to anyone looking for a low cost watch that looks like a million bucks.

reviewText:
I am satisfied that this item looked good. But, I expected that the Rudraksha seeds would look a little bigger than what I got (although I certainly did not expect they would be very big). The string seems a bit fragile (or less sturdy). This looks nice as a fashion jewelry, but my purpose was to wear it in my meditation to get the natural powers of the Rudrakshas.

Also, -- one of my friends that looked at it said that the Rudraksha seeds seemed to be synthetic (i.e., man/machine-made) and not natural seeds. I am not quite sure whether he is an expert, but to my eyes the Rudraksha Maala that he has looks more natural than the one I got from this product.

In summary, if you are considering buying this product -- (1) Ask a question to the seller whether the seeds are natural or machine/man-made. (2) Be prepared for a long wait to receive the product because of the shipping.

I recieved it yesterday, loaded it up with three cards, two business cards and ten bills of cash. It is easy to access just what I need, and I can swap out what cards I'll need in the morning. For instance, I only use my library card once every few weeks. So when I know I'm going to thel ibrary I will slip it in. It can fit easily about five more cards, but I like it not being too tight when I extract a card or my cash.

Anyway, I took it out today for the first time. When I got out of my car, I did my usual butt-pat to make sure my wallet was there and I kind of panicked for a second. There was no lump! My pocket didn't feel heavy. I had to actually slip my hand in my back pocket to make sure it was there. This thing is GREAT. I'm going to order a few more varieties. This is now my wallet company of choice and I'm sold. It's excellent.

NOTE : I ordered the red and black model, and I got an all black model. Not a problem, the all black version looks cool, I just didn't get the exact wallet I ordered. I'm not sure if that's Amazon's fault or Fowfold's fault. I noticed on the sealed envelope it came in inside the Amazon box that it didn't specify the color so it might have been an easy mix-up. For the price I paid, it's not worth sending it back and trying to get the right color, I'll just order another one when I'm ready for a change. Just be aware that you might not get the exact color you request.
Love the slim and lightweight design.  Is easily holding 4 cards/id along with bills in my front pocket.  No bulge or unsightly "signature"-very discreet.  Quality construction. Recommended.
summary: Flowfold pocket card holder wallet rocks

reviewText: I purchased the 1/2ct Diamond Tennis Bracelet crafted in Sterling Silver 7 1/2inch as a gift to myself for Mother's day. It was the best gift I could have gotten myself. The packaging was great I wasn't expecting to receive it so soon, but I was happy when I did. Quality and clarity both are fantastic!!

I'm not really sure what people expect for a cheap diamond bracelet.  My wife and I love this bracelet, though one day will replace it with something nicer with larger diamonds.  At a glance the picture makes it look like you're getting large diamonds encased in metal pattern and that's it.  In reality it's almost all metal with a tiny little round diamond in the center of each area.  The rest is etched with raised bumps to catch the light and break it up.  That raised area is also more white in real life, whereas the photo makes it seem as if it's all a deep silver color.  The stated "list price" is completely for show, but if you get it for less than half that as it's normally priced and aren't looking for something much much more expensive, I think it's a great bracelet that should last a long time and look great.  Just don't show it off to your friends under a microscope.
summary: Great if you understand what' you're getting

This is a gem of a small bag. It's size is deceiving. The fact that the double zipper opens the bag all the way up one side & down the other (you can use one zipper or both), allows the bag to open wide (it has side gussets so nothing falls out). It also has two deep slip pockects, one on each outside (front & back), as well as a slip and zipper pocket inside. The fact that it is taller than wide, allows for a larger cell phone to easily fit vertically inside, and I can carry more than I expect (keys, small wallet/coin purse, lipstick, cell phone, small hand sanitizer, several folded tissues, and even a few more thin items. It also has a very long adjustable shoulder strap so it can easily be worn crossbody even on a tall person. I have this bag in both black and brown. I wish they made more colors, I would buy more! The leather is soft and of high quality, both the inside & outside slip pockets have a nice lining. Zippers work smoothly and the bag is so light you barely notice you have it on. It's a great bag for everyday when you don't want to carry all you own! Super for a concert or night out, or even going for a walk, when you just need a few essentials. Highly recommend this bag!!!

The latest is for children to go barefoot as this is better for foot development, or at least that's the thinking this week. We wanted a shoe that gave some traction but was not too stiff. This fits the bill greatly. Our little one does tend to run a little hot so he does sweat with these on but I think he gets that from his mothers side. That said these are perfect for walking around indoors during the winter and outdoors in spring and fall. Maybe a bit warm for summer.

**Update

After 3 weeks of use, and barely any detectable wear on the soles, the vinyl fabric holding the compression buckle to the shoe started to wear. First the pleather flaked off which exposed the reinforcement threads. This allowed the reinforcement threads to fray on the edge of the oval loop.(See customer photo above) They are hanging on by a thread and neither the seller nor the manufacturer is willing to exchange them as the 30 days has expired.

If our little one had started wearing these right as we got them, we would have been inside the 30 days, but alas we were planning ahead and bought them earlier then he was ready to use them. I do not think the design is bad, and we really like the shoes for the first 2 weeks, I think the fabric used is inferior to the wear it receives. The data from the inside of the shoe is as follows.

China Style # XY8812
MFG Date 05/2013
RN#36769

If you receive similar shoes, with the same date code, I would suggest you return the shoes and ask for a different batch date. Sometimes  this can correct manufacturing or material issues. It is also possible that the sourced fabric is not appropriate at all, which in case would mean they are doomed to fail in similar fashion. I hope the seller or manufacturer steps up and does the right thing with these as the value is not there for 3 weeks of use.

I live on a fixed income, but have "expensive" taste when it comes to jewelry, so I am always on the lookout for reasonably priced pieces that appear far more expensive than their asking price and these Silver Tone Clear Swarovski Elements Halo Dangle Leverback Earrings by SilverSpeck truly fit the bill!
Although they are made of silver toned brass, they have the appearance of real Sterling Silver and the Swarovski Crystals sparkle like real diamonds.
The stones are glued, not pinned, but they are well set and secured.
I love the Flower Design of these 1" x 1/2" dangle earrings!
The addition of a few small crystals on the front of the lever adds to their High Class, Expensive Appearance.
All of the crystals are multi faceted and bounce the light remarkably well.
The leverbacks are easy to manipulate, so they are super simple to put on and remove. I appreciate that the hinges on the levers lock into place, so I don't have to worry about catching them on my hair or clothing and losing one when I wear them for a night out on the town.
I recently wore these Silver Tone Clear Swarovski Elements Halo Dangle Leverback Earrings to a friend's wedding and I received a lot of compliments. My lady friends were very surprised to learn they were not real Sterling and Diamond Earrings!
They arrived in a very nice drawstring pouch which looks and feels like real leather and is handy for travel or storage in my jewelry box drawer.
I received these earrings at a reduced cost in exchange for testing and review and I am extremely pleased to give them my highest recommendation!
summary: Extremely Well Made Silver Tone Clear Swarovski Elements Halo Dangle Leverback Earrings!

We were looking for luggage tags that would fasten securely to our bags, have a tag that is easy to fill out, be unusual enough to spot our luggage easily and not display our information openly. These tags were exactly what we were looking for. They arrived in just a few days, and they were exactly as described. The buckle straps will be more secure than a lot of the other designs we saw for attaching tags. I was able to print the information the information we wanted to put on the tag on regular computer paper using a standard label size, and it was easy to slide the computer paper tags into the tag holder between the cardboard tag that was provided and the window. That means we will be able to change the information on the tags very easily. The tags snap closed, so our information can only be seen when the tag is opened. The only thing I might change is to have the tag itself slide into the holder from the inside rather than the outside of the tag, It would make it just a little bit less likely to have the tag fall out of the holder. I love the fact that we had several different cover designs to choose from, and my husband and I ordered different color tags so we can tell our luggage apart at a glance. I would highly recommend these tags! They weren't that much more expensive than other tags, and they are worth the little bit more money.

reviewText:
I love the GDiapers system.. I started with my friend's small bundle just to try and see if I liked them.  It took me a few weeks get used to them as in the begining, we were gettig pretty requent leaks.  However, I stuck through, bought the Mediums, and hardly ever have a leak since.  I think the reasons we were getting frequent leaks in the small are 1) The cloth inserts needed to be stripped, and, 2) I was fastening the velcro too tight.  Keep in mind, we use regular pampers at night so I do not have to change him every 2 hours.

Since starting on the GDiapers about 8 months ago, I've conviced about 3 other friends to use this wonderful cloth diaper system.. Happy baby, Happy mommy :)

Before my son was born I looked at these and thought they would be wonderful. I bought into the whole gdiaper system. Sadly, they do not work for my son. I get leaks with every pee, to the point that I have to change his outfit and usually mine. I was actually afraid to let other people hold him when he had these on. I did contact the company and did all they recommended and struggled with them for almost a month but they did not get better. I finally had to move on to a different brand out of desperation (My son is in Charlie Bananas and he has only had one minor leak in the last month, very happy with CBs). To compound the problem they were too problematic for my husband to use so I became the only person who changed diapers- nice right. They are very cute and super trim but for me function comes before style. My son also got red marks from the snaps, this seems to be a very common problem. If looking for more info (or used covers) try the Yahoo gdiaper group, I joined when having all my diaper issues and they were a great resource.  Very sad they did not work for me, now getting ready to resell all my gdiaper stuff. Too bad.

This review is more about the incredible customer service.  I don't wear rings, but when I decided to get married I had to do something.  So searching around I found this ring -- which I wanted to make my "practice ring" just to get familiar with wearing a real one.  The problem was getting the size just right.  Here on Amazon the size chart skipped my size.  I tried the smaller one, I tried the larger one.  Neither worked.  I needed that extra .5 space.  So I contacted Cavalier Jewelers directly and spoke with a rep, named Louis.  This guy was a godsend and if I was the boss of that business he would be getting a raise. He found a ring in my size... the ONLY one they had in stock.  And he said he'd make sure the right size would go out if I ordered the size next to it on Amazon (he'd watch for my name & order and swap the right size into the package).

The additional problem was that our wedding was within a week -- like just 4 days and Sunday was one days (we were running late as most weddings tend to do). I already placed the order so I couldn't change the shipping.  I was about to buy another ring and ship it Next Day, but Louis said "No problem," so we just had to trust Louis that on our wedding day I'd have at least my practice ring.  Well, he came through in spades.  We got the ring in time and it was a perfect fit.  Cavalier Jewelers, in my opinion is a good seller and worth checking out.  Trust me, I'm not a shill for them, as I said I'm not big on wearing jewelry.  But I'm STILL wearing that ring.  Yes, it's only a $30 dollar ring, but it's the sentiment that matters.  It has held up well, it is strong and it has some heft to it.  People see it and like it. If it wears down (as other reviewers said) then I can simply buy another one at this price.  I know some might find that sacrilege to the institution of marriage, but the ring is a symbol not the actual concept so I'm fine with that.
summary: Good ring, even BETTER customer service

reviewText:
A great little watch for the price.  I had to send the first one back since the analog portion of the timepiece kept stopping (second hand would "stick," therefore the larger hands would not advance).  Amazon and Asurion were OUTSTANDING in their prompt service and support handling my return claim.  Since the watch malfunctioned after the normal 30-day replacement window, I had to return the defective watch and re-purchase a new one.  The new one has worked like a champ!

The features I really enjoy about this watch are the large digital displays, the contrasting colors between the analog hands and the background, the night backlighting system and the easy of setting the time.  The large digital displays are much easier to read than most digital/analog combo watches and the contrast between the background and the analog hands is such that the time is quite easy to read.  I had previously ordered a more "stylish" looking Casio watch which had a very nice, clean-looking face.  But the analog hands were thin and shiny silver and the watch face was bright white.  It was nearly impossible to read the time because the hands blended right into the background.  And the digital display was so small the analog hands frequently covered up the numbers.  Not so on this watch!

The backlight (when activated) is a soothing, unobtrusive color and a mild intensity.  It doesn't blind you in very dark conditions and the digital readout is very easy to see.

I am in the military and frequently "re-hack" my watch every couple of days.  On this model you simply press one of the buttons 3 times to enter the time set mode (rather than press & hold some button or combination of buttons for some obscure amount of time), then press one other button to reset the seconds to "00."  It's so easy, you could do it in complete darkness, if you'd like.  It's not a perfect time-keeper (but then it was only an $18 watch!), but it's typically not off more than a second or so per week.

I guess my only complaint would be the "luminescent" analog hands.  They are very, very dim, even in total darkness.  They can be read, but you have to look very closely to see them.  This typically is not an issue though, since you always have the backlight function available if you need it.

Overall, I am very pleased with this watch as a low-cost, work watch.
summary: Great watch for a very reasonable price!

It looks very nice and feels like a good quality watch. But it wasn't for me.
Judging by the fact that there was no place for a battery in the back and all I saw were watch gears instead, I gathered it was a wind-up watch. I could not find in the directions any way to wind it up. Apparently the main twisting piece on the side has three "settings" which are very hard to distinguish between and one of them may have been the one to wind the watch. I could never tell if it was working or not.
The other on the same side are, in my opinion, badly placed on the watch. I work with my hands and my wrists get bumped a lot and, as a result, so does my watch. These buttons were pushed a lot accidentally while at work which was very inconvenient. Also, while at work, an especially large bump to my watch CAUSED THE GLASS PIECE COVERING THE FACE OF THE WATCH TO FALL OFF. I would have lost the piece if I hadn't heard it hit the ground.

I bought this watch as a daily casual/semi-formal timepiece that I wouldn't have to worry about being damaged, lost, or stolen. The package arrived in about a week and in good condition, but it wasn't in protective packaging, only wrapped in plastic. Fortunately, the watch was not damaged. At first glance, it has a bit of a Carrera (TAG Heuer Men's CV2010BA0794 Carrera Black Dial Watch) design to it, but without the luxury quality. That being said, everything about the watch case looks more expensive than it really is. The dial details are impressive, with the sole exception of the date window, which is a little too small for the date wheel numbers. Also, the dual second hands aren't exactly in sync, but I suppose this can make the watch look like an automatic chronograph at first glance (auto-chronos usually cost over $1000, so this can be a good thing). The glass scratches easily, which is to be expected with a mineral crystal. The pushers for the month and day functions are good quality, but the crown mechanism is poorly made. It does have three positions: manual wind, date, and time set, but I feel like a few gears are going to break unless I am very gentle with it. The exhibition case back and Krönen & Söhne rotor engraving are nice touches, and the mechanical self-wind movement keeps reasonably good time (gains about 4 seconds per day), though I would be cautious with quality control from a Chinese manufacturer. The power reserve is good, but I haven't exactly measured it. It'll definitely last overnight. The case says it's water resistant, but based on its appearance, I wouldn't test it. It can probably handle a few rain drops but definitely not being submerged. You get what you pay for. The stainless steel bracelet looks great, but the build quality is average at best. The links are loose, and the steel brushing isn't very good, though the double locking fold-over clasp was a pleasant surprise. In retrospect, I probably should have purchased the same watch but with a leather band (Also on Amazon). The watch is eye-catching, and has received a lot of compliments. Overall, for the ridiculously low price (for an auto-watch), this is an excellent timepiece that looks great and performs acceptably.

The really expensive toe socks are great quality, but a waste of money for someone who loses socks as easily as I do. Also I'm poor. But if I buy those super cheap ones from China they disintegrate before I even have a chance to lose all of them. These Fila socks, in my opinion, are the perfect compromise of quality and price. I still have two pairs from almost two years ago (the rest of that package is, alas, long lost) that have been worn and washed gazillions of times and still hold up. They are all the same color so I can match them easily. They fit nicely inside toe shoes, not too thick, not too thin. The only problem with them is that when I lose too many socks of one foot and have to turn one of them inside out to wear on the other foot, the Fila label is scratchy on my ankle, but I won't take away a star for that because it's not Fila's fault I'm such a loser.

reviewText: I love these gloves.  Very comfortable for driving and grabbing things.  I am able to use the touch in my phone!

I bought these as a replacement for another pair of Isotoners I have that are finally falling apart after 10 years. The old pair was a nice spandex with actual leather grips (said leather is now peeling and cracking). It worked well for my winter/cold weather dog walking needs. I figured another similar pair would be just fine. Well, Nope. They've changed their design so instead of the nice smooth, stretchy spandex (like yoga pants), it's a rougher texture and just a little bit stretchy. Okay fine. I can deal with that since I really needed just a pair of lightweight gloves for cool morning walks so my hands don't freeze off holding the flexi-leash. What I really DO NOT like is the old leather grip has been replaced with something akin to rubber (or a plastic-y rubber-like material). It most certainly does NOT grip the leash at all. I now find myself holding onto it with a vise-like grip of death which makes my hand cramp. I'm sure this new material was far more "cost-effective" for Isotoner than using half-way decent leather, but it's s***ty. Rubber, when cold, has none of the traction it's otherwise known for as I've experienced first-hand thanks the my city adding rubber pavers to the crosswalks, which become a virtual "slip&slide" when it snows. I'm glad these are not driving gloves because I would have no control of the wheel as it would slide right through my hands. They are "sort of" warm-ish, but I would never use them for Cleveland winter walks in single digit temps (I have another pair of Columbia fleece gloves for that). These work for the 40-50 degree weather and not much below. Purchase with caution.

I have Carolyn Pollacks cabachon apatite ring and enhancer and chose this when it went on sale to compliment them.  It certainly does that in a big bold way.

I was drawn to this bracelet first because it matched my other items.  Secondly because it is adjustable (I have a 6 1/2" wrist).  Thirdly, because of the superb value.  If you love Carolyn's jewelry please consider this even if you do not have matching pieces.

The stones vary from medium teal blue to dark teal blue.  It would match most any outfit color.  All the stones in my bracelet are of great quality with no dents, dings, or chips.  Some are oval, while others are round and rondel shaped.  There are also ribbed sterling beads spaced throughout the other beads.  The beads are separated by four sterling silver stations that help keep the three strands lined up.  These stations as well as the sterling silver end caps and extender chain are all oxidized.  I am especially pleased with the large lobster clasp which helps me put this on by myself.

A word about sizing.  As I said my wrist is 6 1/2" and it fits great leaving a little dangle room for the extender chain.  However, since the entire length of the bracelet is 9 1/2" I believe it would fit close to a 8 3/4" wrist.

I believe this is a bracelet that is made well enough to tolerate daily wearing.  It is really nice and I am glad I was able to purchase at such a phenomenal price point.

As a gift, the person is really happy with it.  She liked the size, weight, and how it had some extra pockets inside.

My biggest complaint is with the belts and straps. The ones I received are not the ones in the pictures provided by the seller. Also, whether you watch the anime or read the manga, the straps above the waist were inaccurate. Everything else I received was fine, but don't be surprised if you find yourself needing to buy the straps somewhere else.

The costume is accurate- if you're looking at the manga. The costume is, of course, considerably "inaccurate" if you're just watching the series by itself. This aside, it's gorgeous, and I found it worth every cent (because -surprise- I actually bought it). Now, the colors of the recon core symbols are B&W, and so is the scarf. These are the only 'abnormalties,' and if you're not okay with that I wouldn't suggest this product.
If you'd just Google "Attack On Titan Manga," and viewed almost any of the results, you'd see that Mikasa's scarf is BLACK, not RED in the original. You'd also see that the B&W symbols are accurate, also.

But, if you are okay with that, I have some advice and some greatness to share with you. The shipping was amazing and arrived over a week earlier than the ETA. If you don't know how to assemble the belts, you could break a part of them, but ten seconds of hand-sewing can fix that.
My biggest suggestion is that you lie about your size- and I don't mean to make yourself smaller, but bigger. I fudged my sizes to be a little bigger, and the pants were still kinda tight on me. The other thing is that the white used in the shirts and pants are almost see-through, which is another reason to fudge your sizes, because then you could wear a pair of white leggings instead of searching for skin-colored undies all over Walmart or Amazon. Also, there's real beltloops on the pants, so if you oversize on accident, you can use a belt. I'd also suggest an undershirt for the shirt, because it has the same problem of being see-through.

Other than that- despite of that- I really Love this costume! The majority of it fits well and it's really warm- which isn't perfect for warmer cons or events, but it is for Winter events like Halloween or any of the cons through March and February months.

About the price, it's really good. If you view the other search results on this site, people are trying to sell cloaks and jackets alone for up to $50. This includes a full costume, both the cloak and Jacket for only $110ish. It's worth it in my opinion, and if you want a really good Cosplay, I'd suggest this.

Peace

reviewText: Awesome! I have the larger wallet with all the compartments as well as the wristlet with phone slot.  I love both of those as well. Sometimes you need a more compact wallet. The leather is smooth and supple. Lots of spaces for cards! Don't be fooled by the small size! Would order again. Been recommending products to all friends and family! Plus bought a few as gifts as well. Thanks for a great product!!

I bought this wallet to have a sense of security from low-life scumbags trying to use RF to steal information from credit, debit and ID cards, etc.  Liked the style, and all of the card slots for holding ID and cards, ample room for paper money and the exterior change zipper pocket.  It's just the right size too, half way between a clutch and a small wallet. Perfect for me and should nicely fit in my smaller purse. I like the snap closure for the most part. It has two holes in which to snap the wallet shut, which may make it easier when the wallet is a little thicker. The only dislike, which is not that serious, is I have to move it around a little to find a hole for the snap closure.

The company doesn't waste any time shipping out your purchase and I got it much sooner than expected. They are also good at responding to refund requests. I know because the first clutch style wallet I ordered from them had a broken zipper pull, which fell off when I just touched it, because the metal ring attaching the pull had somehow been damaged. The company made the refund easy, so I felt comfortable ordering another wallet from them. The new wallet's zipper pull is different and the metal ring it attaches to is thicker. Much happier with this second purchase.
summary: Good quality wallet with lots of places for cards.

I needed something that would provide better separation in my crotch for comfort. Regular cotton boxer briefs were not cutting it (too much sag) and I'd constantly be trying to adjust myself to compensate. I read the reviews and was somewhat concerned about the quality so I decided to buy three separate brands to compare quality with price. These "7 Pack Mens Multicolor 3d Clipping Fit Stretch Boxer Briefs" were the cheap ones, mid was "2 Pack Kronis Low Rise Trunks Soft Cotton Microfiber", and high end was "Calvin Klein Men's Micro Modal Boxer Brief".

I purchased this 7-Pack in April 2015 and have held up well over the last six months. They are light, provide the extra separation I was wanting, and for the money, are very reasonable. Most boxer briefs in this category are a lot more expensive. They just started to get pin sized holes in one or two of the seams, but for the money I'm very happy with them. They were however, not my favorite brand.

The winner by far was the Kronis. The Kronis boxers feel amazing. They are not very long, however my thighs don't rub together so it wasn't an issue for me. After about a month I altogether stopped wearing my cotton boxer briefs and bought more Kronis, even though they were more expensive. They're worth every cent! The CK boxer briefs are nice (make your package look huge for some reason), however it wasn't as supportive or comfortable in my opinion as the Kronis or 7-Pack.

If you're looking for some inexpensive boxer briefs, I would recommend this 7-Pack. I gave it 5 stars as they have held up over the last 6 months and are well worth the money. They're SO much better than cotton. - However, if you want to spend a little more money for great quality and a very comfortable boxer brief, go with the Kronis. If you want your junk to look great and have the extra cash, CK is your best bet. I actually wear CK the least because they're not as comfortable and I'm married so no one cares what my package looks like. :)
summary: Overall worth the buy, but not my #1 pick.

I don't understand why or how these are called Genie bras, because I bought a real Genie bra elsewhere and it was so much better than these, so different in every tiny detail. I noticed on the bag that these were once marked "XL", and only received a sticker on top of that one that said "L" which was the size I ordered. The first one proved to be too large, and the others were slightly too small, though I'm sure that the two were the correct size and the other was really an "XL", even though all their printed-on tags said "L". I also found that there is an odd bit of sewing in between and at the top of the cups, where a piece of thread is straining the lace that it's trying to hold up. I cut the thread on one bra, and found that the lace isn't long enough to go above the edge of the rest of the bra for that promised "peek-a-boo" (seeing the lace while wearing a top) that every Milana Genie is supposed to have. My officially real Milana Genie bra doesn't need nor does it have a thread that forces it to go beyond the rest of the bra, its lace fits perfectly over it and doesn't fall down, unlike the three I bought here. These bras don't look like the picture provided, nor do they come all that close to the genuine Genie bra that I have. I can't wear these anywhere accept to bed and around the house because of the poor fit, shape, and the lack of a working camisole effect, since they give you a chest wrinkle if you never cut the thread holding up the lace. I don't know where these came from or who made them, but I would be shocked to find out that they are in-fact genuine Genie Milanas.

Unbelievable sexy fit. I bought these maybe 6 years ago at nordstroms rack in medium and still wear them....still tattered but amazing fit after so long. I finally found these online after reverting to various awesome brands...from hard tail to lucy...excellant brands and quality...but this tops all.

1. I am 5'7.5 and have long legs. Makes everything difficult. When i was 135lbs before my pregnancy these were perfect in medium. Today 8 months after a difficult (is there an easy??) Pregnancy, im still at 148 lbs..the large is super comforting and flattering.

2. Compared to all expensive brands ive purchased, these are by far best quality and fit my figure best. My hips are wide from the front and very narrow from the side...i gain most of my weight in the belly and upper side hip. These accomodate exceptionally well. No discomfort and ill likely use them rigorously in future pre/post pregnancy and during fit time in between.

3. The clothe fits the calves and give minor sexy flare. They are closer to leggings with more ankle boot room than flared yoga pants. Ideal for yoga, running, lounge, hikes. Protection and flexability with supurb fabric quality you cant find in sewing shops (and ive looked to try to more frugally replicate).

In short...i don't know if you'll like them if you are short. The fabric may not expand if you don't need the length..but i cant guantee that. But, if you need the leg room and won't tolerate ugly pants, lacking in proper display of arttributes, these are your guys!!

Hope you know what a gift this honesty is...I'd honestly rather be the only one who owns these, struttin about town..or the trail.
summary: still tattered but amazing fit after so long

I was very disappointed with the quality of this card game.  I thought the cards would be thick and durable, like the traditional memory cards we're used to playing with.  But, these cards are not.  The cards are very thin, and if you buy this game, you may want to consider laminating the cards to prevent them from tearing.  Also, this game does not come in a box to store the cards; instead, the game arrives in a plastic bag that needs to be cut open.  So, if you store the cards in the plastic bag, you risk losing some of the cards because the bag doesn't close again once it's been cut open.

reviewText:
I added a couple of photos to illustrate the issues, but both are serious design flaws.  First, the portion you cut to size the belt frays within about a week after each time you cut it, making the buckle fall off --- So you have to cut about a half inch off every couple weeks to get the belt to stay on.

This means, within a couple months, you now have a belt that's too tight, defeating the purpose of the product.

Ironically, the other side with the clicking notches also isn't securely glued close enough to the notches, which makes it impossible to get the belt off using the quick-release mechanism.  This is difficult to explain with text, but take a look at the photos, and you'll see the design flaws.

reviewText:
I bought both this EazyBelt and the slidebelt:http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00DR1EZ8M/ref=oh_aui_detailpage_o08_s00?ie=UTF8&psc=1 at the same time and have used them for about 6 months alternating between one and the other.

Here are the major differences.
Eazybelt:

Much cheaper, but you have to order a specific size.  I ordered my size and wound up a little snug.  Now they offer to fix that, I never really took them up on it, but it's the same offer Slidebelts makes.

The ratcheting mechanism on the Eazybelt I prefer significantly.  It's MUCH quieter than the slidebelt.  Now to be fair, the slidebelt I got may not represent every type of buckle they offer, but when you cinch up the eazybelt, it's very quiet.  The slidebelt is very noisy in comparison.

As for the belt itself, the leather is thick and looks like high quality.  The slidebelt leather doesn't "look" as nice but interestingly it SMELLS of leather.  My wife said this has more to do with how the leather is finished then necessarily the quality of the leather, so I don't know what to say there, but I do like the actual leather smell that the slidebelt has.

My only flaw that I see on both belts is really it's Achilles heel.  The spot where the belt buckle attaches to the end of the belt (the non-ratcheting part) is small.  I don't know what the thinking was, but there are only 5-6 little pins in the middle on both belts that hold the buckle to the belt.  After some wear, I've found it to wear down, start twisting a bit and eventually even tear loose causing me to have to cut a 1/4 inch off to secure it again.  I've also had a few times where it will just pop loose if the belt gets pushed into the buckle by accident and suddenly the buckle is on the floor or hanging off the ratcheting mechanism.  Anyway, my main annoyance with it.  I was able to fix the issue by wedging a piece of cardboard into the end of the buckle mechanism to keep it from popping loose, but wish it did that better on it's own.  There is no torsion on that piece for some reason so it really can be problematic.

Overall thought I still like both these belts.  This belt is thicker and I really prefer the ratcheting mechanism.  The Slidebelt comes in a much fancier case and seems to be a nicer leather, but the ratcheting mechanism is annoyingly loud.
Easy on, easy off.  Fits like a glove.

The main mechanism is easy to use and holds securely.  I worry more about how well the other end of the belt holds to the buckle.  It's basically just a set of teeth that grip into the belt leather.  It hasn't failed me yet, so I'll give it 5 stars.

reviewText:
I  bought my EasyBelt a few months ago, but I do not see the buckle I chose on display now.  Anyway, what I have to say I think applies to all equivalent EasyBelts, whatever the buckle style.  First, I can say that after over more than 60 years of belt-wearing experience, I find this design in a class by itself.

I want to pass on a few tips that I hope will make your experience with it enjoyable right from the start, should you buy one.  Whatever your waist size always order a length at least 4 inches longer.  Once you get the belt and decide how much belt you want extending beyond the buckle, simply cut the buckle-end of the belt to make a satisfactory length.  Don't worry about cutting off the depressions you see made by the buckle holding spikes.  Personally, I think when the buckles spikes penetrate a fresh surface, they make a better hold on the belt.

Some learning is required to unbuckle the belt.  Just remember that the swivel release-latch is on the bottom right of the buckle. Hold the buckle with one hand and swing the release latch OUT away from your body, while simultaneously with the other hand shove the belt IN toward the buckle.  It took me a couple of weeks to get this pattern down in my mind.  Hopefully, you will know it right from the start.  That's swing the latch OUT, push the belt IN.

Further, I like the belt because it's clean in understatement, with the focal point being the buckle.  It can be worn with anything.  There are no distracting holes, or places for frictional wear to show.  The ratcheting system allows for 1/4 inch size adjustments.  Tightening requires only pushing the belt into the buckle.  Loosening requires only swinging OUT the latch while pushing IN the belt, then holding the latch and letting the belt slide out.  I just marvel at how easy these adjustments are, anytime, anywhere.  No one will ever see you unbuckling and rebuckling again.  And the belts - in my opinion, at least -  are by far the best, and for unbelievably low prices.
summary: Best belt for unbelievably low price

I've been climbing about a year, and wanted to upgrade from the entry level shoes I was using.  I gotta say, these shoes are pretty nice, at least at this level.  I instantly felt more confident in my foot placements, heel hooks, and toe hooks.  I was actually able to top a boulder I was having real trouble with just a few days before due to a sketchy heel hook.  I wear a size 10.5 street shoe, and got this in 11.5.  They fit snugly, but not too tight.  There is actually just a tiny bit of wiggle in the heel, but that didn't seem to be too noticeable while climbing.  I could probably go down a half size, but I feel like they'd be excruciating to wear at that point.  They're about as comfortable as my entry level shoe, which I can wear for 2 hours straight without terrible pain.  I like the way the inside of the shoe is shaped to accommodate the "claw" shape that your toes will be in, without feeling like my toes are being smashed.  The rubber is firm, which I like since my other shoes would bend every which way making small footholds troublesome.  The padding underneath the Velcro does tend to get bunched up when tightening the straps.  I'd definitely recommend this to anybody looking to upgrade from a beginner shoe to a more aggressive shoe.
summary: Great shoe for intermediate climbers looking for a more aggressive shoe style.

reviewText: I read other reviews for this shoe before I bought it and as advised I bought a size slightly larger than my street shoes. I wear a 11.5 street shoe so I ordered a 12 and they fit exactly how I want my shoes to fit. They are very tight and slightly uncomfortable but not unbearable. I noticed an immediate difference in my climbing. The stiff toe really sticks to those tiny footholds and I found it very easy to heel hook in these as well. All in all, I am extremely happy with the purchase considering the price. Now the real test begins.... can they live up to regular use over the next several months or years?

The M5s are great shoes for training in the gym and long days outdoors. They fit well and are flexible enough for climbing on slabby walls while still having a snug enough fit for heel and toe hooking without the shoes slipping. The M5s are extremely comfortable and are my go to shoe for warming up, training, and climbing at the end of a session when my feet are tired or sore. They are true to size with other Mad Rocks. I wear a women's size 7 in street shoes and a 5.5 in the M5. The rubber on these shoes also holds up extremely well (I've had a few pairs), mine last 6+ months climbing about 4 days a week, and even then the toe just becomes very rounded and I don't blow a hole in the shoe.

The Mad Rock M5's are my favorite shoe to date. They have excellent performance on all types of rock from Valley slabs, Font slopers to Heuco roofs. Mad Rock continues to improve their product line every year and this is my favorite update to the line.

The rubber is super sticky in cold and warm conditions and has good durability.

Toe rubber is perfect for scummy toe hooks.

The heel isn't extra bulky so it's easy to place and doesn't slide around a lot.

2 Velcro straps make it easy to get in and out of while keeping the fit tight.

Price can't be beat for the quality.

A great sport climbing shoe. In the past I have worn the Evolv Pontas brand, after a full season of wearing them its my opinion that its just as good and the rubber has lasted longer. It really excels in small edge footholds.
summary: Just as good as Evolv Pontas

reviewText:
Comfort:
For me this shoe provides great comfort. I can keep them on for a 2 hour climbing gym session or through long sport routes. There is no concern about pain which I find is a big factor when it comes to climbing shoes.

Performance:
This climbing shoe handles great all types of climbing (vertical, slab, overhangs). I've tested this shoe from the limestone walls of Finale, Italy to the coarse granite in Joshua Tree. This shoe makes trust in your feet a non issue. The aggressiveness on the toe makes overhang climbing easier, well IMO.

Sizing:
If the initial size fits perfectly, I would recommend going down a half size. It may be a little tight at first but it will mold into a perfect fit. I do this because I do not like any dead space throughout the shoe.

Pricing:
Amazing value for the price. No other shoe in the market will provide you with incredible performance and durability for a low price.
summary: Take It To The Next Level

reviewText: After using my friends old shoes for a few sessions which were a more relaxed La Sportiva model(most comparable to the Nago), these made a huge difference in my ability to climb. My street size (10) is the absolute tightest I can get my feet into. If you're looking for a more relaxed fit, I would size up by a 1/2 size. I have pretty wide feet for my size, so I didn't find the toe box to be particulary loose. In fact, it feels tight to me. Having said that, I don't notice any discomfort when I'm climbing. I guess my brain is more focused on "don't fall," rather than "man, my toes hurt." I just climbed in the Gunks with them yesterday and compared to the last time I climbed there, I felt like I was cheating. The stiffer toe made it easy to step up on the tiniest footholds and the sticky soles let me apply opposing force on a corner crack without slipping at all. I'm still very much a beginner and the one thing I noticed is that the sticky (see soft) rubber at the tip of the toe is wearing away. This is probably from my messy form than anything else though, so I can't accurately comment on their longevity.

I have owned lace up Muiras(2 pairs)  Evolv Bandits, Chili Spirits, Mad Rock Flash, ClimbX e-motions. These are the most comfortable(for a tight fit in a climbing shoe) and have the stiffest fore foot.
Because of the stiffness of the shoe you don't lose power when you size them for comfort. And yes, with that stiffness, you probably lose a little sensitivity.
I would compare the rubber to Vibrams Edge.
I wear a 11.5/12 street shoe and have morton's toe. These are a size 12 and are really snug but not screaming, toes curled tight. For an all day trad fit I'd probably go with a 13.
While I prefer a lace shoe, I am happy with the velcro straps.
A GREAT SHOE AT A GREAT PRICE!

Next time you need to climb a technical route where crux requires you to put your feet on almost invisible micro edges put on these Mad Rock M5 shoes and enjoy the maximum level of friction. These shoes do what they are supposed to do, precision at its best! I really enjoy climbing on this shoes.

Well made, and the fleece lining is very soft.  Sizing is about right, based on suggested measurements.  I bought three pairs, two as gifts.  My only negative comment is that one is made a bit differently than the other two.  The difference is in the leather (one seems more 'worn in' than the other two), and the fleece lining isn't as uniform in density and length of the wool fiber.  Possibly the nature of the hide from which the mittens are made, but the contrast will lead me to return the 'odd' one.

Which leads to another comment.  I once had a pair of faux sheepskin mittens that were the warmest mittens I've ever had, but, even though faux sheepskin gloves are available, mittens apparently are not; I can't find them anywhere, in store or on the internet.  I am sorely disappointed not to have an option that's just as good if not better than an animal hide.

Ok, so, all the reviewers that say this is child sized are out of their minds.  I believed them, and wanted a looser fit, so where I normally wear an XS-S in US sizes, I ordered a large in this item, and it is enormous on me.  I'm 5'2, 120, and could've easily fit a small, and probably could've made a medium work with a few minor adjustments.  So this item might run on the small side of US sizes, but don't go wildly sizing up on it or anything.

That said, the product itself is really quite nice, I'm really disappointed it didn't fit so I can't use it this weekend like I wanted to. The fabric is light, but doesn't feel cheap or chintzy.  It's got a nice drape.  The pattern is adorable without being overly cutesy, and it is more navy than it looks in pictures on my screen, anyway.  The shorts, I found, were long, but that could've been a result of my crazy up-sizing.  The buttons seem well attached and the hems are straight without any hanging threads or anything.  The waist has a fake drawstring tie on the front, but it doesn't actually do anything, the waist is elastic.  It opens plenty far to get it off and on without an issue.  And it has pockets, which is always a plus in my book.

The one thing I do have a grip about, and this has less to do with the product, more with the shipping, is it came shipped to me in a gallon-sized Ziplock bag, like someone had purchased it, tried it on, lost the plastic bag it came in, shoved it in the first bag they found from their kitchen, and returned it.  It didn't look or feel or smell like it had been worn or anything, my guess is tried on and exchanged or returned, but it was still very strange to receive a Ziplock bag (with like, a Ziplock pattern on it and the blue slide closure; this wasn't a Ziplock-type bag that the company uses to ship things).

Overall, I love this romper, and may reorder in the correct size.

The kangaroo pockets, well they kept with the frumpy look of the entire thing...to include the starfish zipper pull.  I gently wore this maybe three times during the Christmas holiday, and it started coming apart at the pocket seam. Unraveling, I guess that's why it comes with a little plastic sleeve of thread. I ordered the bracelet to replace an old Celtic braid bracelet that had broken and lost links. It's an unusual link pattern I happen to like as it feels very smooth yet looks rugged. The stainless steel looks to be good quality and will last without colour change or tarnish, so I'm happy about that. On the minus side, the individual links - which are really a twisted "V" shape to form the chain - are not all closed at the top, most have a small gap that occasionally catch on each other. The bracelet also has a strange twist at one point which looks to be a seam or joining between two longer chains, which could just be a one off from manufacturing, i.e. having a long spool of the braid before cutting to size - my luck to catch the bracelet with the seam - or it could also be the result of a particularly bad catching of the unclosed links. Either way, it not really noticeable, I just happen to know its there. All in all, it's a nice bracelet, very masculine without looking garish, and as I said the braid feels good on the wrist. In general it's a 4-star, but I take 1 star off for the seam.

reviewText:
This charm is super cute and exactly what I was looking for at a great price! It arrived in quickly and in excellent condition. I love the lobster-claw clasp on it which makes it very easy to attach it to a charm bracelet or necklace without any additional tools or the need to visit a jeweler. I chose to use my charm to decorate my Midori Traveler's Notebook and it not only looks great I really appreciate being able to just clip it on without having to re-string the elastic and I can just as easily move it to other notebooks and planners. It has been on the notebook I carry with me for almost a month, in and out of my purse everyday, and there are no signs of dulling or chipping on the enamel and the back is still shiny and pretty with no dents or scratches.
Planner charms are very popular right now and there are dozens to choose from in craft stores and hundreds available online but it is very hard to find Hello Kitty, especially in blue. This one is different than everything else out there and really nice quality. I am looking forward to more of these charms to match other planners, to add to my charm bracelets, and give as gifts. Highly recommended!
summary: Super Cute, Very Sturdy, Great Price!

Simplicity Womens Winter Warmer Infinity Scarf

Okay, so twenty-some years ago I met a guy that had the broadest shoulders, the most gorgeous eyes, and the most insanely delicious walk that I had ever seen. To this day Im still amazed that he asked me to go out with him. I fretted over that first date for a week and did all of the things that you do when you have a first date with an Adonis. I wish there were a lot of details that I could skip over here but frankly, there aren't  my beautiful fringed scarf got caught in the door of the car, the valet started driving off, and I was unceremoniously humiliated and almost strangled before we were ever greeted by the matre d. The Adonis did eventually call me again (and I ended up stealing enough of his sweatshirts over the following year that he had to marry me to regain custody of them), but I had sworn off wearing long warm scarves forever. The Simplicity Neck Warmer Infinity Scarf is the perfect way for me to get all of the cozy warmth of a beautiful neck scarf, without risking near-death and total embarrassment at the hands of an overworked valet.

This beautiful scarf is made in a texture-patterned knit that feels lightweight but provides exceptional warmth. At 23 inches long it gently drapes at the neck creating a flattering neckline that works perfectly with any coat or jacket. 16 inch width allows for coverage of my neck and chest, and can be drawn up to cradle my jawline and ears, or my entire head, when it is really chilly outside. The delightfully soft acrylic knit maintains shape and doesnt sag or get stretched out from use. This scarf is also extremely versatile  it can be worn in a multitude of ways to suit the weather, or to give any outfit a fashion-forward update.

I received a sample of the Simplicity Winter Warmer Infinity Scarf at no cost in exchange for an unbiased review and love the beautiful design, the high-quality material, and I especially love how wonderfully versatile it is (and that Im safe from hurried valets)!
summary: Gorgeous warm knitted Infinity Scarf that creates a flattering neckline, is well-made, and is extremely versatile!

He prescribed I switch to a front pocket wallet or to something thinner.  This one works well in the front pocket, or is thin enough to carry in a hip pocket without stressing the alignment.

This is a great thin wallet.  Practical.  Great value.  Durable.  A couple of bonuses: 1) water resistant fabric is better than leather when you may need to drop it into a damp bathing suit pocket or are engaged in a sweaty summer activity. 2) the tiny slots over each card pocket are perfect for holding a toothpick or two.

reviewText: Prior to purchasing this wallet, I had owned and used leather wallets which despite being far more expensive, I found I needed to replace every couple years due to wear and tear. After using it for just a few days, I realized how much I preferred this wallet's thin profile, and I never returned to using my other more costly leather wallet.  After having used this product everyday for nearly two years, it still looks brand new.  This wallet's construction and functionality is excellent for what it is, and I recommend it very highly.

reviewText: Great slim wallet. I bought several different wallets at same time and this is the one I still use. Very minimal, durable and fits my front pocket.  Holds 5+ cards and my cash.

If you desire a slim wallet. This is the one to get. It definitely does its job. It's made of a stiff nylon sailcloth type material so it is extre thin. It's good for traveling as it can fit unobtrusively in a front pocket. The only reason tha it's not 5 stars is that after about a year and one-half, the stitching starts to unravel. But is a nice wallet. I would get another one.

I'm really liking this wallet. It's replacing a Tyvek wallet of the same size, which only lasted me about a year. This nylon wallet feels much more durable, but the material isn't noticeably thicker than Tyvek, which is great. It's a little floppy, which takes some getting used to, but doesn't bother me at all. There are rubber pads inside the credit card pockets to keep cards from coming out, which adds some slight bulk (and seems unnecessary, since the cards shouldn't be able to slip out of a closed wallet anyway), but after a month of daily use, I haven't been bothered by the extra thickness.

This is definitely a minimalist wallet, with only two pockets for credit cards, one pocket for cash, and no ID window. If you prefer more organization, you're going to be disappointed, but if you want to forget you even have a wallet in your back pocket, this is a great buy.

This wallet is awesome! I have tried many wallets before this one and I have finally found the perfect one!

I was in the market for a wallet that is SUPER thin and also highly functional. I wanted to carry a lot of cash, and also hold 7 to 10 cards. I love this wallet because the cards will never fall out since the opening fro the card slots are facing inward when folded, there is also some rubbery grip on the inside of the card pockets because nylon is super slipper, this keeps the cards snug. I also LOVE how there are only two card slots without material in between each card, making the wallet the thinnest I have ever seen even when fully packed.

The only thing I was worried about was that this wallet would not look classy since it is made from nylon, and I was wrong. I feel like the nylon pattering on the wallet looks more elegant and clean than leather does and it doesn't end up looking like a kids wallet.

I had the leather version of this same "sport wallet" from ALL-ETT before I purchased this one. I like the nylon version much better. In the leather version the nylon and the leather seemed at odds with each other and the stitching connecting the two materials came apart after 3 years of use. I like the nylon version better because it is thinner and it doesn't have the same seam as the leather version where the stitching came apart at the edges, so I anticipate it will last much longer.

For such a good price I am VERY happy with the quality.
summary: This will be my go to wallet for life now. Looks classy.

Very disappointed, will not order from this company again.

The coat comes with 2 zippers and the coat snaps throughout the length of the coat. I had trouble in the beginning zipping the coat.  Then it would get stuck. Next, that 1 zipper came off and broke.  Well, I had one zipper left on the coat and figured I could zip with just that 1 zipper.  Not a chance!  I then went to Hobby Lobby to buy a replacement zipper.  No such luck - there were too small for coat.  I don't want to take it to the cleaners and spend more money to get zipper replaced.  Although I could snap coat, it still does not keep all of the cold out - the whole purpose of buying this jacket - especially when you have to stand out in the cold for 15 minutes every day in the morning.  The coat is very beautiful - I love everything about the coat except the zipper. Although I don't mind much of hardly any wiggle room, the zipper problem is the reason for 3 stars.

While the size selected was 8, it indicates a size "L."  I suppose the size 8 is equivalent to a "large?"  Anyway, it JUST fits, not too much wiggle room.  However, it is fine with me, because I prefer it to fit.  So, anyone that wants some extra room might want to size up!

She is around 5'8" and we still had 3" on the floor with her heels on.  My suggestion would be to allow time for alterations if needed.  My daughter didn't mind and looked so amazing in this gown....There was No Way she wasn't going to wear this dress!!!. This dress would flatter any figure and the material fell around her waist and hips perfect!!!  I loved the workmanship and Ever Pretty's dedication to a quality product.  If you are looking for a dress/gown, buy from this company. I recently purchased this jacket from the local REI store, for just about the same price it is currently listed at here on Amazon (I purchased the black jacket as shown here; note that it is also available in other colors at this separate listing on Amazon --> Marmot Men's Hawkins Jacket Blue Night/Dark Ink). This is a sharp looking, well made, warm jacket. It has just the right amount of insulation and wind protection for my needs in our winter climate here which is moderately cold with very limited rain or snow, but lots of wind. The sleeves are a bit long, which may be how clothing is made these days. That is about the only fit issue worth mentioning. The sleeves are lined so that the jacket can be worn over a regular shirt or sweater and your arms will fit within the sleeve without bunching up. I will see how this jacket wears over time, and if I find any other points worth mentioning here as I use it, I will return to this review and update it accordingly.
summary: Sharp looking and well made, with just the right amount of insulation and wind protection for my needs

reviewText: I had to cut the elastic waste band and they fit fine. I bought these pants because they are the new style and I usually have an issue with my thighs in pants and have to go up a size in pants just because of them. Example is that I can fit a size 20 in dresses but in pants I have to go up to a size 24w or 26w just to fit my thighs and feel comfortable and end up with this weird gap in the back of my pants where I have to worry about my crack showing if I don't wear a belt. In these pants it was the opposite. They fit like an XL instead of a 2X there was some looseness in the thigh but not enough to call it a genie pant anymore and the belly was tight. The problem was that they don't sell a larger size. So I made a small cut in the fabric and removed the elastic and they look great with tops that come below the belly area. For 9.99 and how they feel on I would buy more.

Using this wallet to hold a field notes booklet instead of a passport. I did have to trim the booklet about 1/8" or so to get it to fit correctly. The only issue I have with the wallet is that the card pockets are good, but I have to make sure that I have 3 or more cards in them so that they hold well. The rubber grip gets dust on it and then it is not as...grippy...It does take a little getting use to the extra height of the wallet, but other then that its great.

Minimalist wallet, I use it everyday in the cargo pockets of my pants. It is unnoticeable until I need it.

I also used it to carry my passport when 2 weeks abroad.

It is not the kind of wallet that you want to be spending cash out of, as that function is awkward, due to the flimsy layers. However it serves well as a means of holding emergency cash.

Paying with card is smooth and I keep receipts in the opposite pouch until end of day for expense report. In which I transfer them to a folder.
Holding more than 10 receipts would be to much.

Very thin, lightweight and water resistant (verified with lots of sweat for walking 4 miles). It's the smallest passport wallet (of all 3 dimensions) I can find on market and can easily fit into all pant pockets.

It has no hard exterior so you'd need passport inside to keep the shape. Only two card slots but each has  no problem carry like 4-5 credit cards - however it feels rather weird. I still prefer to have one card per slot. Not wide enough to hold long boarding pass - you'd have to fold them.
Needs more card holders

very compact and efficient use of space.  This is great if you want a Passport holder that does not add BULK to your luggage or pocket.  I can easily put my passport, cash and cards in this and still be able to put it in a rear pants pocket or a jacket pocket.  It is THIN and lightweight, which would be great for people backpacking or traveling on foot around foreign countries.  It has a tiny bit of rubbery substance that helps keep the cards in place so they don't slip out.  Would buy again.  I really like it and recommend.

I bought this to replace a similar wallet I had for easily 10+ years. I received this one in April, and one of the zippers popped off in August. Half of my stuff is stuck in the wallet with no way to open it. While this wallet design may not be for every one, I'm fond of the design as it works for me; however, I'm disappointed in the quality of the zippers on these. I'm going to contact the manufacturer to see if they any suggestions on how to open it and fix the zipper, or if they will replace it. If they do nothing then I will probably drop my rating to one star as I will have to buy another after less than 6 months of owning it.

Update 9/6/14: The company replaced my wallet for free. So I've upped my rating by a star for good customer service. The new wallet is several shades lighter tan than the original and the one pictured here, but that does not bother me; however, others may want to know that the color may vary a bit. We ended up cutting the original wallet to get my stuff out as the zipper teeth held strong despite having a tug of war with it. So long as the zipper pull tabs don't come off this should last a very long time.

This is the second running skirt I've bought and I love it!  It has a boy-short under the skirt, not a bikini type brief like the other review states.  It has a small pocket on the front that is perfect for a gel, key, ipod, or even a small cell phone.  The best feature for me though is the drawstring!!  Most running skirts are just an elastic waist.  Since I'm a bit curvier I've had trouble finding a skirt that fits both in the waist and in the hips.  With the drawstring I don't have to worry that the skirt will slip down while I'm running!

The boy-short is made of spandex with elastic at the leg openings but it is not a true compression short.  The skirt is made of the same fabric that most running shorts are made of (sorry, not sure what it's called).  There is a small slit in the front by the stripes for added ease of movement.

Overall this is a great skirt and I'm planning on buying another one in a different color!

reviewText: Just a great watch.  Does everything you need a digital watch to do.  Incredibly durable, you can chuck it at a brick wall.  Great for swimming and working out.  Is also perfect for rugged conditions like desert, forest, etc.

I bought this for my husband (older but same model) on our honeymoon 18 years ago.  It still works and he has only had to replace the battery about every 5 years.  The watch is so old that even though it works just fine, after wearing it to a physically demanding job for 18 years 5 days a week, the rubber around the bezel is disintegrating.  So I am getting him a new one.  I can't tell him because he loves his old one so much that he would tell me not to!
it looks great, it does its job, its relatively comfortable, it was exactly what i was expecting, i have had for couple of months now, pretty happy with it

I've been through hell and back with this watch these past four years (bought this back in 2010 on Amazon for ~$45 with Prime). When I go surfing, I strap this watch right on top of my wetsuit. When I go lap swimming, I have this watch on. At the gym, while I fish, while I snowboard, on my backpacking trips, camping trips, hikes, you name it. Even in the shower. I rarely take this watch off - only to let my wrists air out once in awhile overnight.

I've had this watch for nearly four years now, and it finally broke on me last week. Well, namely, the bottom strap where the strap meets the small metal spring-loaded attachment tube. It was my fault really.. I was.. in an impromptu, friendly wrestling match with my friend and we got too rough. I believe too much pressure was applied on the watch strap, and it snapped at the point of contact to the main watch computer.

Well, the watch still works - I just need to buy a replacement strap. In conclusion.. great watch - really built tough. If you plan on entering saltwater with this watch, just make sure you rinse it with freshwater after (i.e. just wear it into the shower). Some white powdery buildup may appear after a year or so, so just get some toilet paper and a toothpick to get it out. Overall, sturdy watch. Although it does look a little bulky if you're a relatively skinny person. I'm only 5'9 and 150lb and I sometimes felt this watch was a tad bulky on me (gets in the way while wearing fitted dress shirts, tighter long-sleeves, etc). But still got a few compliments on the watch.

But in the end, I think what matters most is the wearer of the watch - and I was definitely satisfied with this watch, especially since it was so affordable. $45 for a watch that can last you 4 years (and counting) through hell and back? I'm sold.
summary: Sturdy watch, but perhaps I was too rough on it

reviewText:
October 14, 2015

I'm somewhat of a wallet hound. Always looking for that perfect solution. For years I carried a large hipster because I tend to carry allot of cards and cash. That quickly became a pain in the you know what. Literally. So I started my minimalist journey. I really like the Bellroy wallet line and have a couple of those. The problem was there is still too much leather. I read about a rubber band being the best wallet of all time but I didn't like having what I was carrying completely exposed to every stranger's casual gaze.  And after all it was just a rubber band. Not very sophisticated. Money clips and other small wallets couldn't hold enough cards. Then I saw the Moneywrap. I've had it a couple weeks now and I think it may actually work out. It's rubber band meets the leather wallet. It can handle the 10 cards I carry and cash easily. It took a little getting used to for me but it's become pretty natural now and I can handle my cards and cash now without dropping something when I open the moneywrap. A little pricey for a strip of leather, a stretchy band one might use to put their hair in a pony tail and a clip to hold the band to the leather strip. It does come with two extra stretchy bands as those will likely wear out much quicker than the leather piece. But it works. Pretty clever actually. I bought another one so I would have a spare.

November 21, 2015 update

I don't normally provide updates but I felt like it was warranted to help make sure the money wrap doesn't get a bum wrap. As one of the reviewers mentioned the money wrap is small but that is the intent IMO. This is a minimalists wallet. I also don't blame the other reviewer's first impression. This is small and appears to not be very secure. But after 6 weeks of use the wallet does work although in a non traditional way so it takes some getting used to. I have 10 cards and 16 bills in mine right now and it's no where near maxed out. If you get this you need to be prepared to have an open mind, really give it an honest try and want a minimalist wallet. I plan on using mine as my primary carry for the foreseeable future. But again, I want the smallest wallet possible that can still hold allot of cards and bills.

reviewText:
Unbeatable for the price.  I needed replacement behind-the-head ear muffs that I wear over the ear-flaps of my winter fleece cap.  I like the added layer of warmth, and without a chin strap, the ear muffs keep the wind from sneaking in under the flaps and giving me ear aches.

When I saw these for such a remarkable price, I decided I'd give them a try - and without any choice of color, I ordered two at once.  They came with reasonable delivery time considering the distance and cost - about the earliest "expected" delivery date.  Both pair were back.  The salient points if you are considering these for your gear:

1. They are the lightest weight of any ear muffs I have ever tried.  The frame is not plastic as I have come to expect, but a tough and resilient single-wire loop that forms the ear cups and then crosses over between them to form the connecting bridge.

2. They are contoured to fit my head - with a well-defined "up-and-down" geometry.  The "up" side is wider, to fit the cranium, the "down" side is narrower, to conform to the narrowing of the neck.  I have not tried to re-shape them, but I suspect it may be possible that the wire framing.

3. They do NOT fold - unlike most plastic-framed models that have a hinge rivet and can fold because of it.  On the other hand, my other pair of ear muffs broke at that hinge rivet because of the inherent weakness at that kind of stress point.

4. They do NOT telescope/slide wider or narrower - again, because they are a solid-wire frame inside.  Then again, once properly adjusted, they won't be accidentally changing on you, either.

5.  At the same time as I ordered two pair of these ear muffs that took a few weeks to ship, I also ordered a far more expensive name brand that is highly rated and came via "Prime."  I do like it, and it IS a higher grade of construction and materials - but I got TWO pair of these Womdee ear muffs for about 1/3 the cost (with shipping included) as the "fancy" ear muffs - and while I have ended up using both kinds, my Womdee muffs are seeing more action these days.

So, to wrap up my own experience, I two pair of these for a very low price - and I am glad I did - and find them perfectly suited to adding an extra layer outside the ear-flaps of my winter hat.

summary: Worst purchase I have made in a long time...

reviewText: thumb ripped open hours after opening the gloves. they were warm; and they looked pretty nice, aside from the torn thumb.

The gloves work wonderfully to keep my hands warm and I love that they actually fit my hands! My hands measure 7" from tip of middle finger to the base of my hand (hand meets wrist), ~7.25' in circumference and 2.5" in diameter. Perfect fit and very toasty. The only reason I give these gloves a 4 and not a 5 is b/c the suede isn't sewn on fully and undoing the mitt portion while the gloves are on is quite difficult. Maybe the latter will get easier with time and more usage, but for now, I have to take my thumb out the glove to undo the mitt off the button. The only thing that completely sucked was the price of shipping which was almost as much as the gloves themselves. But in looking at other comparable products and their prices, I still came out cheaper overall ($10 for gloves + $7 in shipping.)

The quick and simple on these is that they are alright and worth the money. With that said, I've only had them for about a month. On one of the gloves, the inside liner has ripped from the base area so sometimes a finger will slip to the outside of it while putting them on. The "hood" cover on the other glove as torn on one side where it mounts. Both gloves are already showing signs that the brown palm cover won't be there much longer. I don't baby the gloves, but I'm not out shoveling gravel with them either. With the condition of them, I figure they will at least get me through this winter and maybe one more. I'm sure I could throw a stich around the palm cover and the hood corner and they would be close to 100%, but for the cost, I think I would just purchase a new set after these go out. If your looking for high quality duribility, look elsewhere. If you looking for a product that's good for the money and nice and warm, then these might be the ones for you.

I bought this for my 6yr old son who is really into monsters and it couldn't have been a better choice for him!  He loves them and wears them every night!  He would wear them into bed if he could, but I make him take off his "monster feet" before going to sleep! The top is soft plush material and the claws are made from shiny, textured vinyl cloth.

 * * THINGS THEY DID RIGHT * *
(+) Well made, tops are plush material, bottom seems durable and so far has worn well
(+) The style makes it very forgiving for fitting different sized and shaped feet.  It is sort of like having a big pillow strapped to your foot.
(+) CUTE STYLE!  It will make you smile, guaranteed, when you take the pair out of the box and likely every time you slip your feet into them.

 * * THINGS THAT COULD HAVE BEEN BETTER * *
(-) Nothing I can think of,.. for the price and design, a very solid idea and execution.

BUYING SUGGESTION
If you are looking for cute, plush house shoes that will likely hold up to some abuse and fit well, this would be a good purchase option.. buy them, have a laugh, and enjoy!
